===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|effigie}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|effigiēs||likeness, effigy}}, from {{m|la|effingō||represent, portray}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɛfədʒi/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|effigies}}

# a [[dummy]] or other [[crude]] [[representation]] of a [[person]], [[group]] or [[object]] that is hated.
# a [[likeness]] of a person.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|a likeness of a person}} {{l|en|figure}}, {{l|en|image}}, {{l|en|picture}}

